&lt;p&gt;Mitratech is growing through acquisitions, and each deal brings a new set of financial data that must be understood, transformed, and accurately migrated into our core systems. We&#39;re looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Senior Finance &amp;amp; Data Analyst&lt;/strong&gt; to join our Post-Merger System Integration (PMSI) team and own that process end-to-end.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is not a traditional finance role, and it&#39;s not a traditional data role. It sits right in between. You&#39;ll need to understand how acquired companies recognise revenue, structure their contracts, and run their billing operations — and then use that understanding to transform their data into formats that work inside Salesforce and NetSuite, in a way that&#39;s clean, compliant, and audit-ready.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate comes from a finance or accounting background and has developed a strong affinity for data — someone who is as comfortable interrogating a messy dataset as they are reading a revenue schedule. You don&#39;t need to be a software engineer, but you do need to be highly analytical, independently motivated, and genuinely curious about how businesses work.&lt;/p&gt;
